1. Introduction and Motivation
Stability governance frameworks for autonomous systems must do more than prevent invariant
violations — they must measure and exploit the transient coherence of multi-layer internal states
to accelerate recovery and tighten control during periods of high self-consistency. Prior
governance frameworks (QBN v7 and earlier) lacked a coherence measure capable of
distinguishing two states with identical spectral deviation but very different internal
representational alignment.
Consider two systems sitting on the boundary of the admissible set. System A has layer states
that are mutually consistent — all pointing in similar directions in the representational manifold.
