This finite ceiling is a direct consequence of the dimension-normalised layer norm, preventing
runaway coherence accumulation under adversarial loading.
3.3 Finite Epoch Duration
A critical safety property: hyper-coherent epochs are finite in duration. Once the Taleken gate
closes (Δ ≤ 0), the ultra-kernel becomes zero and TSC(t) falls below θₕ in at most:
K_hyper = ⌈(θₕ − TSC_floor) · (n+2) / δ_decay⌉ steps
This finiteness is a governance safety property, not a performance limitation. An unbounded
hyper-coherent epoch would indicate the system never exits the inadmissible region. Finite
epochs confirm the governance architecture successfully resolves the spectral violations that
drive them.
