9. Limitations and Future Work
Several limitations of the current framework are acknowledged. The hyper-coherence threshold
θₕ, boost factor α_TSC, hyper-coherence bonus βₕ, and GREEN amplification factor 1.05 are
currently set heuristically. A principled calibration method — potentially via Bayesian optimisation
or an information-theoretic argument connecting optimal coherence thresholds to spectral
admissibility margins — is deferred to future work.
Proposition 3.1 (TSC monotone increase in GREEN) is stated for constant sinusoidal input.
Extension to stochastic σ-bounded inputs via a martingale argument for the layer-state norm
evolution is a stated objective. All results are currently from software simulation; hardware-in-the-
loop validation on a UAV flight controller and a cyber-physical gateway is the next experimental
milestone.
The TSC functional treats layer norms additively. A richer model incorporating pairwise cross-
layer coherence terms would capture interference effects between governance layers, potentially
revealing constructive and destructive resonance phenomena beyond the additive model.
Machine-verified proofs of the core theorems in Lean 4 or Z3 are also identified as a priority.
